title: Subtitle Fonts
description:
SUBTITLE FONTS
--------------


 Tiresias Screenfont

 - A typeface designed for TV subtitling.
 - Maybe the best font for film.


 Fago Normal Regular

 - A nice font for subtitling movies.


 Bitstream Vera Sans

 - A generally good font for video subtitles.


 ITC Officina Sans

 - Officina was designed for Office documents
   produced on medium-resolution printers - 
   works well in captioning and subtitling.


 Zurich

 - Font from Bitstream TV Font Pack library.
 - Works very well on the screen and is very readable.


 Letter Gothic 12 Pitch

 - Font from Bitstream TV Font Pack library.


 Mayberry Pro Semibold

 - Mayberry was designed for use in set top TV devices.
